1
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,480
Before I assign the work,

2
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,329
I have an announcement to make.

3
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,520
The leaders just held a meeting and decided

4
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:23,720
that the launch window for our Haoyue-4 has been moved up.

5
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,579
Zhang Ziming, Li Yanyan, You Xiu,

6
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,120
you three need to leave immediately

7
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,079
for Xichang to assist with the launch site work.

8
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:30,880
Yes.

9
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,120
Regarding the far side of the moon,

10
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,280
for the whole world,

11
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,540
it is actually uncharted territory.

12
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:41,840
This is actually an opportunity for us to stop following others.

13
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,079
to an opportunity to lead others.

14
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,280
Right?

15
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,420
Now, the situation is,

16
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,240
the Space Research Institute reported

17
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,400
that the work on Yutu-2 is not going smoothly.

18
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,079
They need us to cooperate with Dr. Xu

19
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:55,920
to resolve the lunar rover's software system issues.

20
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,160
By the way, speaking of Dr. Xu,

21
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,160
let me interject.

22
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,040
This Dr. Xu

23
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,440
is a typical all-rounder.

24
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,800
When you work with him,

25
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,060
make sure to learn and communicate more.

26
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,540
They will all be all-around warriors in the future.

27
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,120
Wu Wei, Ziqi.

28
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,250
Starting today,

29
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:17,519
you two will assist with the work in the inner test site.

30
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,959
Is this a secondment?

31
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,720
For the Haoyue 4 mission,

32
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,360
will our Muxing team work separately?

33
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:27,160
What's wrong? Can't you work if you're separated?

34
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,240
In the future, the driving of the Yuetu rover

35
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,880
might also be handled by you two.

36
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:41,000
Let's go. We're heading to the inner test site now.

37
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,320
Alright. As for the rest of you,

38
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,610
let's finalize the landing site plan.

39
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:49,760
The landing area has basically been determined,

40
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,290
which is within the South Pole-Aitken Basin.

41
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,640
Jiang,

42
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,560
you are in charge of finding the landing site.

43
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,220
Jiajia, you'll be the backup.

44
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,850
Let me emphasize again,

45
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,180
the landing site plan is crucial.

46
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,000
It concerns the progress of the entire mission.

47
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,560
We must, before the window closes,

48
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,690
complete this task.

49
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,770
We guarantee to complete the mission.

50
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,680
Currently, I think

51
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,720
the most suitable primary landing site is the Zhihai Basin.

52
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,720
First, directly opposite the Zhihai Basin

53
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:20,120
is the Yuhai Basin, where No. 3 once landed.

54
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,640
This is also the basin about which we have

55
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:23,240
the most comprehensive data.

56
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,880
Secondly, within the Zhihai Basin,

57
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,840
there is the second lunar geological example.

58
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:27,880
It is, so far,

59
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:30,810
one of the few geological examples outside of Earth.

60
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,600
Xiao Qu, Caibao,

61
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,360
work with me to organize the data.

62
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,440
Okay, Mr. Jiang.

63
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,159
Jiajia,

64
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,720
how are the three alternatives on your end?

65
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:41,240
Currently,

66
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,320
Apollo and Schrödinger are more suitable.

67
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,760
The third one is still being selected.

68
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:45,680
We are tight on time.

69
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,280
Hurry up with the selection.

70
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,490
Xiao Qu, Caibao.

71
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,360
For Ms. Chu,

72
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,440
if she needs anything,

73
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,800
coordinate with her at any time.

74
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,530
Understood.

75
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,020
All the equipment here

76
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:35,920
is designed to simulate

77
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,600
the real lunar surface.

78
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,120
Unite to shoulder the sacred mission of collecting lunar soil.

79
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,840
The low-gravity simulator in the middle

80
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,360
applies a reverse pull on the rover

81
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:46,720
to offset 5/6 of the gravity.

82
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,480
This achieves the same

83
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,140
low-gravity environment as the lunar surface.

84
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,409
Many devices on the lunar rover

85
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,420
are closely related to light.

86
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,000
Since there is no atmosphere on the moon,

87
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,860
we used a composite array of multiple light sources

88
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,680
to achieve full coverage of solar spectral components

89
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,000
and different solar altitudes

90
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,330
under various illumination conditions.

91
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,860
The simulated light array

92
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,000
is the sun in the test field.

93
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,760
What about the lunar soil?

94
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:20,520
Fake.

95
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,560
These were given to us by foreign countries.

96
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,760
Simulated from 0.5 grams of lunar soil.

97
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,650
Looks just like the real thing.

98
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,560
Rest assured,

99
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,120
we will definitely bring

100
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:36,840
the real one back.

101
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,360
Mr. Qin.

102
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,640
Are these two

103
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,200
the people you found for me?

104
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,960
You should know each other,

105
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,360
so I won't introduce you.

106
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,400
We've met a few times.

107
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,530
From now on, you'll work together.

108
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,450
Take your time talking.

109
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,730
Happy cooperation.

110
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:05,960
Dr. Xu.

111
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,240
Meeting is fate,

112
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,800
and meeting again is even more fate.

113
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,280
We'll be working together from now on.

114
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,040
Please advise us.

115
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:12,600
Yes,

116
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:15,880
let's put the rocket model incident behind us.

117
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,760
Are you done?

118
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,600
Follow me.

119
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,520
Look at this,

120
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,200
the Yutu rover in the test site!

121
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,800
So cool.

122
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,680
Navcams

123
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,320
are for 3D imaging.

124
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,040
And there's the panoramic camera.

125
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,370
It has both panchromatic and color modes.

126
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,080
Not only can it capture

127
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,600
parts of the solar panel,

128
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,640
but even the tracks of the Yutu rover

129
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,570
can also be clearly photographed.

130
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,040
Hello, rabbit. I'm Wu Wei.

131
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,240
This is Ying Ziqi.

132
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,520
We will be your drivers from now on.

133
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:14,130
Please advise us, and let's achieve great things together.

134
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,600
Laser point array.

135
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,000
It uses laser pulse echoes

136
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,160
to measure the distance between the lander and the lunar surface.

137
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,620
Lunar Penetrating Radar.

138
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,640
It explores the shallow geological structure through electromagnetic waves.

139
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,560
You're wrong.

140
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,360
That's the infrared spectrometer.

141
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,240
It consists of a visible and near-infrared imaging spectrometer,

142
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,000
a short-wave infrared imaging spectrometer,

143
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,160
and a calibration and dustproof component,

144
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:38,360
used to receive the reflections of lunar surface materials

145
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,600
for infrared spectral component analysis.

146
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,480
The directional antenna

147
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,400
is a key component of the communication system,

148
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,880
mainly used for efficiently transmitting scientific data

149
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:48,240
and maintaining stable communication with the relay satellite.

150
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:48,880
And

151
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,290
you are not the drivers.

152
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,200
I am.

153
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,210
We will cooperate well.

154
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,640
Let's get the ugly truth out first.

155
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,880
The rocket competition was just for fun.

156
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:03,240
Fun is fun, but this is work.

157
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,000
Since you are seconded here,

158
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,200
you are my people now.

159
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,120
I am very strict about work.

160
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,580
I hope you can pull yourselves together.

161
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:11,760
No problem.

162
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,960
Wu Wei and I discussed it before we came.

163
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:17,040
The biggest problem with our rabbit right now

164
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:19,200
is that the actual data and the computer simulation

165
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,160
have too big a gap.

166
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:20,760
We think

167
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:23,040
there is a problem with the operation subsystem.

168
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:23,880
So we analyzed

169
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:25,280
the eight links of the subsystem.

170
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,200
Although we can't be sure

171
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,280
exactly where the problem is,

172
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,200
what we can be sure of is that

173
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,040
the brain, cerebellum, and ears

174
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,840
must have problems.

175
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,050
Are you done?

176
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:43,240
You don't need to worry about any of this.

177
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,960
The specific plan for the subsystem

178
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,160
I will handle myself.

179
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:48,280
Just help me organize the data.

180
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,480
Any problems?

181
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,520
No.

182
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,250
Then I'll wait for your compiled data.

183
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:04,080
Why do I feel he is a bit...

184
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,120
Geniuses

185
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,930
always have some weird quirks.

186
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,160
Genius.

187
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,240
Open the door.

188
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,080
Just stay here.

189
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,160
Jiajia.

190
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,600
China Aerospace.

191
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,080
These are the books you left at my place.

192
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,680
I brought them back on my way.

193
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:36,920
Thank you.

194
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,880
Don't take what happened to heart.

195
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,400
To be honest,

196
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:46,200
about Mr. Gu's arrangement this time,

197
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,200
I don't really approve of it either.

198
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:57,820
Let me tell you, they are also short of hands in Xichang.

199
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:59,100
I'll talk to Lao Qin

200
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,840
and have you transferred there as the head.

201
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,050
Yanyan happens to be there too.

202
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,480
You two have been partners for so many years,

203
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,960
so you will definitely work well together.

204
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,080
I just think

205
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:11,000
this opportunity is very important to you.

206
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:30,520
No need.

207
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,540
Don't get me wrong.

208
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,930
I really don't mean anything else.

209
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,720
I just feel

210
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,320
that here,

211
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:42,100
you can't reach your full potential like you could over there.

212
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,600
I know what I'm doing.

213
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,520
Who was it that said

214
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,080
they wanted to stay on the front lines?

215
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,280
And who said

216
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:52,480
they wanted to step up to the next level?

217
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,520
You refused to even marry me,

218
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,690
just to do backup work here?

219
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:05,880
Are you done?

220
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,640
If so, I'll be leaving.

221
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,520
I didn't mean that.

222
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,080
Jia.

223
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,650
What a coincidence.

224
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,000
Why are you up in the middle of the night

225
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,200
flying a kite?

226
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,810
And it's a ghost face. Quite scary.

227
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:47,140
It's not a ghost face. It's a smiley face.

228
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,490
Look at it from my angle.

229
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,140
See for yourself if it's the same.

230
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:04,920
This is the difference between

231
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:06,560
expectation and reality, right?

232
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:07,720
Did you get scammed?

233
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:08,980
Come on, you try it.

234
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,800
How does this...

235
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:17,360
Let it go slowly.

236
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:18,960
Let go a bit.

237
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:19,920
Wait a minute.

238
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:21,940
Why are there two balloons on top?

239
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,600
There's no wind today,

240
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,860
so I'm giving it a hand.

241
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:28,560
You can fly a kite even without wind.

242
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:39,840
Jia.

243
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,520
Although my kite

244
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,960
might not be that satisfactory,

245
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,440
but

246
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,000
I think it served its purpose.

247
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:58,120
Have you always been full of ideas since you were a kid?

248
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,840
Jia, do you think

249
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,570
I'm here to coax you?

250
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,800
I'm a grown woman. I don't need coaxing.

251
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,130
Do you think I'm a child?

252
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,640
I knew you weren't the type

253
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,520
who needs coaxing.

254
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:15,000
So whether it's the primary or backup option,

255
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:19,240
as long as we find the right landing spot,

256
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,240
we can safely put the rabbit up there.

257
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,760
Not bad, Mr. Wu.

258
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,320
Since becoming a regular employee,

259
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:28,080
your awareness has really improved.

260
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:28,840
It's alright.

261
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,040
Keep up the good work.

262
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,920
Run.

263
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:35,840
Run and let it go, like this?

264
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,770
Run and let it go.

265
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:38,960
Slow down.

266
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:39,800
Slow down.

267
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,440
It won't fly without wind.

268
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,480
I'll help you.

269
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:44,920
There it goes.

270
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:46,320
It's up. It's flying.

271
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,800
Run.

272
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,840
Just in time, Dr. Xu.

273
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:58,800
Today's data.

274
00:15:59,160 --> 00:15:59,890
Put it there.

275
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:01,280
You...

276
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,440
Do you want...

277
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,240
Do you want to take a look?

278
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,600
If it's not okay, we'll do it again.

279
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,320
No need.

280
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:12,800
This part of the data needs to be recalculated,

281
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,930
and the parameters need to be changed.

282
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,760
Is there a problem with our data?

283
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:18,840
No, the plan has to be scrapped.

284
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,360
You guys can get off work.

285
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:22,840
Why the plan?

286
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,320
Forget it.

287
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,560
He's not willing to communicate.

288
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,960
Let's just cooperate for now.

289
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,360
How are we supposed to cooperate?

290
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,400
We wasted a whole day.

291
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,000
They just change it on a whim.

292
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:42,600
No way.

293
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:47,040
We can't just sit here and wait. We need to figure something out.

294
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:47,920
Figure something out.

295
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:49,450
What are you planning to do?

296
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,480
We should take our ideas for the subsystem

297
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,610
and put them together into a proposal.

298
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,280
Let him see our true level.

299
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:01,040
Let him know what it really means.

300
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,440
That's all well and good,

301
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:04,200
but he said

302
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:06,890
he's going to be in charge of the plan himself.

303
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,359
True.

304
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,240
Wait.

305
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,800
It's not wrong for us to do extra, right?

306
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,000
He can't possibly scold us for that.

307
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,920
This is a battle for the honor

308
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,000
of our Muxing team.

309
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:26,599
We have to show him what we've got.

310
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:29,400
Beat who?

311
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,760
Who? Beat you?

312
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,240
Xu Xu, of course.

313
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:38,380
What's wrong with him? Is he very strong?

314
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,360
Let me put it this way.

315
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,360
You just left the beginner's village,

316
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:46,880
level one, no gear, no skill points.

317
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:49,650
Then you run into a max-level boss right away.

318
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,400
Good lord.

319
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,370
Brother Wei,

320
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,200
how do you plan to beat him?

321
00:17:58,760 --> 00:17:59,920
First, I'll...

322
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,760
You'll help me.

323
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,330
You're not going to fight, are you?

324
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,040
We don't do that nowadays.

325
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,560
With my small frame,

326
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:15,400
the most I can do is shout.

327
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,120
You know?

328
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,130
You just enjoy watching the drama.

329
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,220
You don't know how hard it is until you're in charge.

330
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:24,600
Wei.

331
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,280
You have it hard, but so do we.

332
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,440
You have no idea.

333
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,800
Mengyao is my main supervisor now.

334
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,520
When she and Jia

335
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,280
assign me tasks,

336
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,210
I don't know whose to finish first.

337
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,200
At a time like this,

338
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,130
you are still thinking about that?

339
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,840
What is the top priority?

340
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,360
Haoyue 4

341
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,760
is our first task since we became full-time.

342
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,000
We must do it well.

343
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:47,600
Yes, you are right, Nan.

344
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:48,600
Just eat.

345
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,520
Right.

346
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:13,960
What do you think?

347
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,480
I think it's okay. What about you?

348
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,440
I think it's fine too.

349
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,280
No matter how strong he is,

350
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:23,400
he should know what's good.

351
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:27,320
Let's show him a thing or two.

352
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:31,920
There's still time. Check it again.

353
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:05,720
Wu Wei.

354
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,360
We've got the data ready.

355
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,690
Is there anything else you need help with?

356
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,480
Reset to zero.

357
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,060
Is this voided too?

358
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:22,920
Last night we went over

359
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:24,320
the case you overturned.

360
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:26,640
I found there are still parts that can be upgraded.

361
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:28,770
It shouldn't be dismissed so quickly.

362
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,400
So we made another

363
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,330
subsystem plan.

364
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,620
Who told you to do this?

365
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,360
We didn't take up any working hours.

366
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,680
If you think our plan doesn't work,

367
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,610
we'll accept it.

368
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,600
We just want to demonstrate it to you.

369
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,640
Let's use scientific methods to verify the truth.

370
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,600
If we lose,

371
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,930
we are at your disposal.

372
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:52,400
Okay. Understood.

373
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,210
You want to compete.

374
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:57,690
You're just not convinced.

375
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,760
The obstacle avoidance system is working.

376
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:57,970
Image recognition and data downloading are normal.

377
00:21:58,680 --> 00:22:00,410
The subsystem is also working.

378
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:14,410
What's going on?

379
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,160
It looks like we lost.

380
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,680
Not looks like. We did lose.

381
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:00,240
This might be the perfect plan.

382
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,680
Perfect?

383
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:07,680
Your definition of perfect is way too low.

384
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,120
This isn't the most perfect one.

385
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,040
The obstacle avoidance response

386
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:19,360
can be even faster.

387
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:24,080
With great power comes great responsibility.

388
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,090
I came here for one purpose,

389
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,480
which is to make the perfect plan.

390
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,740
It has to be foolproof.

391
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:37,440
How about it? Are you two convinced?

392
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:42,560
Can you just settle down and work on the data for me?

393
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:46,640
Okay.

394
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,680
This is my standard.

395
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,840
If you can adapt, stay.

396
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,280
If you can't,

397
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,000
leave.

398
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:55,920
We won't leave.

399
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,400
Good.

400
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:04,880
Help me calculate the data of the subsystem

401
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,880
and give it to me tomorrow morning.

402
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:07,640
Got it.

403
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:15,600
Wu Wei,

404
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:18,200
didn't you just say

405
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,720
that if you lose to me,

406
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,520
I can do whatever I want with you?

407
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,210
The two of us.

408
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:29,200
Please rest assured.

409
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,080
Old Qin and I will keep an eye on all the work

410
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:32,280
and the progress.

411
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,240
We'll make full preparations.

412
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:36,000
We guarantee there will be no mistakes,

413
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,640
and absolutely no regrets.

414
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,540
I'm relieved to hear you say that.

415
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:41,480
By the way.

416
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,280
This...

417
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:46,520
You just had four young people join.

418
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,360
You can give them a chance to train.

419
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:48,760
Right.

420
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:49,800
We handed the landing site task

421
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:50,530
over to them.

422
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,920
And there are two kids

423
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:53,200
who offered to take on major roles.

424
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,040
We said okay.

425
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:54,800
So we gave them the tough task

426
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:56,930
of overcoming the Yutu rover problem.

427
00:24:58,040 --> 00:24:59,100
That's the spirit.

428
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:01,920
In aerospace, you have to be bold.

429
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,460
Being bold is fine.

430
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,100
What we fear is cowardice.

431
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:07,970
It's great to assign newcomers to the Yutu rover.

432
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:11,120
They can learn and communicate across departments.

433
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:12,360
Our work

434
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,880
inherently requires multi-department coordination

435
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,240
and joint efforts.

436
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:21,200
We are noobs!

437
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,240
What's going on?

438
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,360
We are noobs!

439
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,080
Hello, sir.

440
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:27,680
Ziqi.

441
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,600
We are...

442
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,080
Hello, sir.

443
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:36,280
I'm so sorry, sir.

444
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,720
You asked me to take a video.

445
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,560
How can I catch up with you?

446
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:45,080
Sir.

447
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:45,760
Hello.

448
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:46,960
What are they...

449
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,410
These are the two kids who just joined.

450
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:53,040
Good. Very energetic.

451
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:53,960
Yes.

452
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,120
They said

453
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,520
they are 'noobs'.

454
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:57,280
What does that mean?

455
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,120
It means...

456
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,000
I'll tighten their strings later.

457
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:00,880
They shouldn't learn all this nonsense.

458
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:01,560
Right.

459
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:02,820
We were all young once.

460
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,080
There's no need for that.

461
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,360
Give young people room to shine.

462
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,240
Yes.

463
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:11,240
We old folks need to keep up with the trend

464
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,760
and learn more.

465
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:13,960
Learn more.

466
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,400
Yes.

467
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,400
Come, please.

468
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:21,120
Why are they early?

469
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:22,920
Why are you causing trouble too?

470
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:31,880
We are noobs. We are noobs.

471
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:32,640
Our Brother Wei

472
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,800
is a big celebrity in Space City today.

473
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,560
You really stole the show.

474
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:37,680
Let me interview you.

475
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:38,960
What does it feel like

476
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:40,440
to walk right into the lion's den?

477
00:26:40,440 --> 00:26:42,520
Can you stop rubbing it in,

478
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:43,320
please?

479
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,760
But it's not embarrassing to lose to Xu Xu.

480
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:46,820
Not embarrassing?

481
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:49,360
He's no ordinary person, I tell you.

482
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:50,720
How so?

483
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,040
What makes him special?

484
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,080
I heard there's a trend online lately called

485
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,600
paying for knowledge.

486
00:26:58,200 --> 00:26:59,640
Just tell me, will you?

487
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,330
Can I get an extra piece of cake?

488
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:06,320
Two cups of milk tea, and an extra piece of cake.

489
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:08,960
Thank you.

490
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:09,920
Go.

491
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:18,760
Tell me.

492
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:20,880
I heard that

493
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:23,800
this Xu Xu was Haoyue 3's

494
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:26,080
youngest chief designer back then.

495
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,320
Younger than Qin and Gu.

496
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,040
He was also the pilot of Yuetu 1.

497
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:33,920
Really?

498
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:35,560
Why are you questioning me?

499
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:37,440
How could my information be fake?

500
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:40,480
It seems he has quite a background.

501
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:42,880
Even though he's not much older than us,

502
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,720
he's still our senior.

503
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,400
I knew he was good,

504
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,920
but I didn't expect him to be this good.

505
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:51,840
Since he designed No. 1,

506
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:54,170
the requirements for No. 2 must be higher.

507
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:57,480
Find a time and an opportunity

508
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,240
to go pay him a visit.

509
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:01,720
I'll dig in.

510
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,400
I have an idea.

511
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:21,120
Let's go find Xu Xu.

512
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:21,720
What?

513
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,360
I know how to win him over.

514
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,680
A model of Yuetu-1.

515
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:28,960
Stop messing around.

516
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,080
I don't have time for jokes.

517
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,600
I'm serious.

518
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:32,280
Let me tell you.

519
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:34,280
My informant told me

520
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:36,960
that Xu Xu was in charge of Number One.

521
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,480
So it's normal that he has higher requirements

522
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:39,360
for Number Two.

523
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:42,240
And it's understandable that he keeps rejecting our plans.

524
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:43,800
What does that have to do with you giving him a gift?

525
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:45,440
Of course it matters.

526
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,280
This is my favorite model.

527
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:52,880
I'm exchanging my sincerity for his.

528
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:55,200
From now on, work will go smoothly,

529
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,530
and I can learn from him.

530
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:57,600
It's worth it.

531
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,680
If our skills aren't as good, they just aren't.

532
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:00,440
Instead of doing this,

533
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,160
you should focus on the plan

534
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:02,800
and let your abilities speak for themselves.

535
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:04,960
Didn't you acknowledge his abilities before?

536
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,160
I do acknowledge him,

537
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,840
but you shouldn't act like this.

538
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:08,720
What did I do?

539
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,880
Is it wrong for me to learn from him humbly?

540
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:11,610
No, it's not,

541
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:13,970
but you need to do your own part well first.

542
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,080
I get it.

543
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,240
You see him stealing your thunder,

544
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,900
and now you're starting to...

545
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:20,080
You want to compete with me, right?

546
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:21,600
I'm not competing with you.

547
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:23,640
You're competing with Xu Xu.

548
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:24,800
And if you compete with him,

549
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:26,800
you're competing with the mission.

550
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:28,440
I am not.

551
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:32,400
I know you too well.

552
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,040
You've always been number one.

553
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,960
Now that Xu Xu has taken first place,

554
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:38,760
you're upset and getting jealous, right?

555
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:39,720
I'm really not.

556
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:41,680
I just want to do the task well.

557
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,080
Who doesn't want to do the task well?

558
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:44,720
Fine, fine, stop talking.

559
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,680
Go deliver it if you want. I'm not stopping you.

560
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:47,810
You'd better not go.

561
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:50,380
I'm afraid you'll ruin things for me.

562
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,220
What are you doing?

563
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:20,400
I was

564
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:23,690
just passing by.

565
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:27,600
Do you need me for something?

566
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:28,000
No.

567
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:29,800
I just wanted to ask

568
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:32,130
if you have an internal meeting tomorrow.

569
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:39,360
If you have a question, just ask.

570
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:40,080
I don't.

571
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,880
Like I said, I'm just passing by.

572
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:42,540
Passing by.

573
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:50,490
Are you sure?

574
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,600
If you kindly invite me,

575
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:56,060
