781
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:22,960
Eat up.

782
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:25,600
Use a spoon.

783
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:39,010
How is the taste?

784
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:40,580
Not bad, right?

785
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:45,280
Ziqi.

786
00:40:50,120 --> 00:40:50,640
Ziqi.

787
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,160
Why do you think

788
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:56,480
aerospace is the most romantic thing?

789
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,400
I think

790
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:04,320
we are engaged in

791
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:06,240
an endless endeavor.

792
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:08,320
Human history,

793
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:10,520
compared to Earth's 4.6 billion years,

794
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:12,480
is just a drop in the ocean.

795
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,280
Yet we

796
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:16,440
use our limited lives

797
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:19,680
to pursue an endless cause.

798
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:24,040
Isn't that romantic?

799
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:29,600
We humans,

800
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:32,120
since we were monkeys,

801
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,080
have been looking up at the stars.

802
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:36,160
Looking up there.

803
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:37,000
What...

804
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:39,640
What is up there?

805
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:40,920
When can we

806
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,440
